<title>Announcement: OpenSSL version 1.0.1a</title>

<h1>Announcement: OpenSSL version 1.0.1a</h1>

OpenSSL - The Open Source toolkit for SSL/TLS<br>
<a href="http://www.openssl.org/">http://www.openssl.org/</a>


<p>
The OpenSSL project team is pleased to announce the release of version
1.0.1a of our open source toolkit for SSL/TLS. This new OpenSSL version
is a new feature release.  For a complete list of changes, please see
<a href="http://cvs.openssl.org/getfile?f=openssl/CHANGES&v=OpenSSL_1_0_1a">http://cvs.openssl.org/getfile?f=openssl/CHANGES&v=OpenSSL_1_0_1a</a>.
<p>
The most significant changes are:
<ul>
  <li> Fix for ASN1 overflow bug CVE-2012-2110
  <li> Workarounds for some servers that hang on long client hellos.
  <li> Fix SEGV in AES code.
</ul>

<p>
We consider OpenSSL 1.0.1a to be the best version of OpenSSL available
and we strongly recommend that users of older versions upgrade as
soon as possible.  OpenSSL 1.0.1a is available for download via HTTP
and FTP from the following master locations (you can find the various
FTP mirrors under <a href="http://www.openssl.org/source/mirror.html">http://www.openssl.org/source/mirror.html</a>):

<ul>
    <li><a href="http://www.openssl.org/source/">http://www.openssl.org/source/</a>
    <li><a href="ftp://ftp.openssl.org/source/">ftp://ftp.openssl.org/source/</a>
</ul>

